# Best Practices Demonstrated

- Clearly define the audience.
- Specify the desired output length.
- Include measurable requirements.
- Define the writing style and tone.
- Require essential content.
- Specify formatting expectations.
- Keep instructions concise and unambiguous.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Adding clear constraints significantly improves the quality and consistency of AI-generated responses. Instead of relying on the model to infer user intent, well-designed prompts explicitly communicate expectations regarding audience, structure, tone, content, and formatting.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

Experiment with multiple versions of the prompt to measure how individual constraints affect the final response and determine which constraints provide the greatest improvement in output quality.

